column40:
 Carbon tax entered into force on January 1, 2025.

Decrees 1050 and 1061 from June 2024 make the following adjustments to the CT:
•	 Entry date of the CT is postponed until January 1, 2025;
•	Indirect emissions are eliminated as subject to the tax;
•	Carbon black, Chlorofluorocarbons and Hydrochlorofluorocarbons are included as subject to the tax, and sulfur hexafluoride is eliminated;
•	When the obligated subjects have more than one fixed source, they must accumulate the emissions they generate to determine the tax payment base;
•	The resources collected may be allocated to the Public Environmental Fund and the Climate Change Fund;
•	The government may grant fiscal incentives to prevent environmental damage, promote technological innovation and the use of clean energy, encourage tax collection, job creation and economic development;
•	The date for the presentation of the annual declaration is modified to the last business day of August of the following year of the financial year in question.
